<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-11-15</DATELINE><TITLE>Errors, Uncertainty, and Ethical Issues</TITLE><BODY>Various medical giants have admonished us to “do no harm,” and yet as we swim in waters of uncertainty, errors do happen. Physician author Lewis Thomas praises restraint in health care, and Arthur Bloomfield reminds us that in our quest to help some, there are no patients we cannot harm.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>